AR_Drone_Autonomy

This repository contains code contributed by students at UH Maui College to the basic setup from the edX course "TUMx.AUTONAVx.2T2015"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ENVIRONMENT:

Control computer OS: Ubuntu 12.04 LTS
ROS version: Fuerte

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INITIAL SETUP:

Install Ubuntu 12.04 LTS (link: http://releases.ubuntu.com/12.04/ )

Follow the instructions in ./AR_Drone_Instructions_Webpage/AR_Drone_Instructions_Wiki_edX.html
(originally taken from https://courses.edx.org/courses/course-v1:TUMx+AUTONAVx+2T2015/wiki/TUMx.AUTONAVx.2T2014/ardrone-instructions/ )

Clone this repository into ~/workshop/autonavx_ardrone/ardrone_python/src/ by opening a terminal and running the following commands:
$ cd ~/workshop/autonavx_ardrone/ardrone_python/src/
$ git clone https://github.com/UHMC/AR_Drone_Autonomy.git

Done!

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A DEMO QUICK-START (After INITIAL SETUP):

Connect to the access point created by the drone
Open a terminal
$ roscore
Open another terminal
$ rosrun ardrone_autonomy ardrone_driver
--------------------------------
(optional; displays real-time sensor data)
Open another terminal
$ rostopic echo /ardrone/navdata
--------------------------------
Open another terminal
$ roscd ardrone_python/src/AR_Drone_Autonomy
$ python ex_takeoff_turn_land.py

Done! To close, go to original terminal, press Ctrl+c, and then close all other terminals

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
